### READ
### ============================================================

### List all users
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users

### Paginate
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users?page=2&limit=2

GET http://localhost:3000/api/users?page=2&limit=2

### Get single user (replace with real ObjectId)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/69e88456e1fe893351274ebf

### Invalid ObjectId format
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/69e88456e1fe893351274ebd

### Non-existent ObjectId
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/000000000000000000000000

### ============================================================
### UPDATE
### ============================================================

### Update name (replace :id)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/users/69e88456e1fe893351274ebf
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "Johnny",
    "lastName": "Updated"
}

### Update bio
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/users/69e88456e1fe893351274ebf
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "Johnny",
    "bio": "Updated bio"
}

### Update email
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/users/69e88456e1fe893351274ebf
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "johnupdated@example.com"
}

### Update to duplicate email (should fail)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/users/69e88456e1fe893351274ebf
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com"
}

### Update non-existent user
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/users/000000000000000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "profile": { "firstName": "Ghost" }
}

### ============================================================
### SEARCH
### ============================================================

### Search by username
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users?search=Jane

### Search by firstName
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users?search=Jane

### Search with no results
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users?search=zzznoresults

### Empty search query
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users?search=

### ============================================================
### FOLLOW / UNFOLLOW
### ============================================================

### Follow user (replace :id with User1 id, :targetId with User2 id)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/69e88456e1fe893351274ebf/follow

### Follow same user again (should fail — already following)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/follow/:targetId

### Follow yourself (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/follow/:id

### Unfollow user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/unfollow/:targetId

### Unfollow someone not followed (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/unfollow/:targetId

### Unfollow yourself (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/unfollow/:id

### Follow non-existent user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/follow/000000000000000000000000

### ============================================================
### FOLLOWERS LIST
### ============================================================

### Get followers of a user
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/followers

### Get followers of user with no followers
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id/followers

### Get followers of non-existent user
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/000000000000000000000000/followers

### ============================================================
### PASSWORD NOT IN RESPONSE (check these manually)
### ============================================================

### Password should not appear in create response
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "checkpassword",
  "email": "checkpassword@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "profile": { "firstName": "Check" }
}

### Password should not appear in read response
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id

### Password should not appear in update response
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/users/:id
Content-Type: application/json

{ "profile": { "firstName": "CheckAgain" } }


